The paper deals with the behavior of approximate message-passing (AMP) in linear sparse estimation problems such as compressed sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of structured operators such as Fourier and Hadamard ones suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SP). The mention of spatially coupled operators and their efficient reconstruction in compressed sensing suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.MM) or learning (cs.LG). Finally, the mention of sparse superposition codes suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
